and its various Gods, It fashioned a Shadow which <br>
many people would call a Soul.  This Soul was formless.<br>
<br>
It was platinum-colored, almost invisible, tremulous,<br>
and it looked like a cobweb floating and changing its<br>
shape in midair.  The Nameless was pleased with Its<br>
work, and It declared that the Soul be cared for by<br>
Luclin, the Maiden of Shadows.<br>
<br>
This soul was me.<br>
<br>
One day the Maiden asked me, &quot;Look at Norrath.<br>
Tell me what you see.  What interests you the most?&quot;<br>
<br>
I looked at the forests of Faydwer and the High Elves.<br>
I said, &quot;Luclin, they love Nature and even worship it,<br>
but is that their ultimate end?&quot;  If it was, I did not want<br>
to follow them.  Natural things like the grasses and trees<br>
died eventually, as they should for new blossoms to grow.<br>
<br>
I looked at the Dwarves.  &quot;They're so serious!&quot;  Their<br>
world was so brown and so rocky, and the only things<br>
that were red were the Rubies that their deity, Brell <br>
Serilis, liked.  Gems glittered there, but to me they<br>
lived in a world of strict order, complete devotion to<br>
their kin, and a great sense of honor.  I feared them.<br>
<br>
I feared many races.  The Iksar were scary, as were<br>
the Ogres and Trolls.  The Dark Elves were frightening,<br>
too, though I was drawn to their bluish-black forest of<br>
Neriak and the indigo gleam of their Ultravision.  Neriak<br>
was a world of Shadows and Darkness.  I liked that,<br>
as did Luclin.  Innoruuk, however, scared both of us.<br>
<br>
When I had finished looking at all the races and places<br>
of Norrath and decided I liked mysterious worlds, <br>
things of bright colors scattered here and there, and<br>
rather neutral races like Gnomes and Humans the best,<br>
Luclin the Mistress took me into her cupped hands.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am going to place you upon this world of Norrath in<br>
the form of a Cleric,&quot; she said.  &quot;You will heal the wounds<br>
of the injured and battle Undead.  As a Priestess, <br>
you will command unspeakable power.  Only you and<br>
the Paladins will be able to call back the souls of Living <br>
players from the Threshold between Life and Death.&quot;<br>
<br>
I was pleased.  Luclin had given me great power indeed.<br>
<br>
She smiled and let me float down to the streets of a city.<br>
Lying there, trembling, but warm and happy with <br>
anticipation, I waited humbly to see what form I would take,<br>
giving thanks to the Maiden of Shadows for her decree...<br>
<br>
I knew someone would find me.  But whom?<br>
<br>
The suspense made my translucent self tingle with vigor!<br>
